        "content": "<p>I opened the namespace <code>CategoryTheory.Limits</code>which brings in the notation <code>prod</code> for products of elements in categories (<em>not</em> products of categories).  But in the file <code>BinaryProduct.lean</code>, right below the abbrev <code>prod</code>, they have</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/-- Notation for the product -/</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">notation</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\" ⨯ \"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">prod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>so I assumed that I could use that notation, but somehow it's not working:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">ε_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℰ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">×</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟶</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ω</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(Application type missmatch, I think it believes that <code>×</code> refers to products of types.)  But when I replace it with</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">ε_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℰ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">prod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟶</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ω</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>it's working just fine, although <code>prod</code> and <code>×</code> are defined in the same file in the same section?</p>",
